The wind whipped through the desolate landscape, carrying with it the mournful howl of a lone coyote. The moon, a pale orb hanging low in the sky, cast long, dancing shadows that seemed to writhe and twist in the eerie glow. As the icy wind bit into his skin, the traveler huddled closer to the flickering embers of his campfire, his heart pounding with a mix of fear and adrenaline.
